questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application is leaking memory in its `AuditContext` (which uses a `ThreadLocal<String>`). You identify the following `Bug Hunter` snippet in a `@Service` class:

java
@Service
public class OrderProcessingService {
    private final AuditContext auditContext;

    @Transactional
    public void process(Order order) {
        auditContext.setContextId(order.getTraceId());
        try {
            this.internalUpdate(order);
        } finally {
            auditContext.clear();
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void internalUpdate(Order order) {
        // Database operations here
        if (order.isInvalid()) throw new RuntimeException("Invalid Order");
    }
}
